ther people delete their app over it or just don=E2=80=99t feel good about =
using Facebook, that=E2=80=99s a big issue that I think we have a responsib=
ility to rectify.=E2=80=9DThe response that struck me the most, though, was=
 this exchange with Recode (https://www.recode.net/2018/3/22/17150772/mark-=
zuckerberg-facebook-content-policy-guidelines-hate-free-speech), which Kurt=
 Wagner broke out into a separate article:

=E2=80=9CWhat I would really like to do is find a way to get our policies s=
et in a way that reflects the values of the community, so I am not the one =
making those decisions,=E2=80=9D Zuckerberg said. =E2=80=9CI feel fundament=
ally uncomfortable sitting here in California in an office making content p=
olicy decisions for people around the world.=E2=80=9DBut then Zuckerberg sa=
